<item>
            <title>[LU-8257] Update error if /etc/mtab is a symlink</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8257</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a bit of rehash of &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1833&quot; title=&quot;Don&amp;#39;t update mtab if it is symlink&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-1833&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-1833&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; / &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-2168&quot; title=&quot;mount.lustre: addmntent: Invalid argument:&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-2168&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-2168&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; with a twist.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That patch checked if /etc/mtab is a symlink to /proc/... and if so skipped the update.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Well, now on Fedora 23+ (and possibly even F22) /etc/mtab is always a symlink to &quot;../proc/self/mounts&quot;, the leading &quot;../&quot; throws our logic off and needs updating&lt;/p&gt;</description>
